The paper deals with natural language processing and neural networks, which are typically covered in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks and bidirectional long short-term memory networks, which are commonly used in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to discover linguistic rules, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves the evaluation and comparison of different models, which is relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
